1 2. On an application for a protective order by the victim of
2 domestic abuse within one (1) week of the incident; or
3 3. Given as testimony of the victim of domestic abuse made at a
4 hearing on application for a protective order,
5 shall be admissible in pre-trial or post-trial criminal and juvenile
6 delinquent domestic abuse prosecutions including preliminary
7 hearings, prosecutive merit hearings, or hearings on the revocation
8 of probation or acceleration of a deferred judgment.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
